OL,3,GWales
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FAfter a chilly and cloudy
OL,6,Fstart, there will be plenty of dry and
OL,7,Fbright weather around by Sunday
OL,8,Fafternoon. Breezy near southern
OL,9,Fcoasts, but winds easing during the
OL,10,Fday. Cooler than Saturday with
OL,11,Ftemperatures below average for early
OL,12,Fto mid-May.
OL,13,
OL,14,CTonight:FA bright evening to end
OL,15,FSunday, however cloud will build from
OL,16,Fthe north with showery outbreaks of
OL,17,Frain reaching North Wales by dawn.
OL,18,FChilly under the clearest skies.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
